<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06117015 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06117015 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  BOOK; WRITING; FRAUD; CONTROVERSY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  &quot;Just Killing Time,&quot; the novel with the phony endorsements from authors Johnle Carre and Joseph Wambaugh, appears to be dead -- for the moment, at least.;   New York publisher Simon andamp; Schuster, which two weeks ago bid a record$920,000 for Derek Goodwin's first novel, about a serial killer, on Thursdaywithdrew its bid because of the bogus blurbs.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  General News  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  FAKE ENDORSEMENTS CATAPULT BOOK OUT OF PUBLISHINGLINE-UPSIMON andamp; SCHUSTER DROPS NOVEL WITH BOGUS BLURBS  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     &quot;We must be able to rely on the validity of what is submitted to us,&quot; saidCharles Hayward, president of Simon andamp; Schuster's trade division. &quot;We havetherefore notified the author's agent of our decision not to go forward.&quot;;   Hayward added that no contract had been signed and no advance had been paid.;   Peter Lampack, the agent for the author, who submitted the book under thepseudonym Derek Van Arman, said Thursday that Goodwin regrets the publisher'sdecision.;    &quot;He maintains his innocence with respect to the fraudulentquotes,&quot; the agent said, &quot;and will be seeking another publisher for hiswork.&quot;;    Several other publishers have said they would consider publishingthe book, which has received enormous publicity in the two weeks since leCarre called his putative endorsement a &quot;straight fraud.&quot; All agreed, however,that they would offer significantly less than Simon andamp; Schuster.;    Severalother publishers bid for &quot;Just Killing Time,&quot; including Bantam Books, therunner-up, which bid $850,000.;    Goodwin consistently has deniedmanufacturing the endorsements from le Carre, supposedly sent by telegram fromEngland, and from Wambaugh. A so-called endorsement appeared on lettersbearing Wambaugh's letterhead, but with a wrong address.;    Goodwin hasmaintained that he was &quot;blind-sided, completely duped,&quot; either by someone whoapparently had a grudge against him or by a former CIA agent he said he knewslightly.;    Before canceling the contract, Simon andamp; Schuster had demandedthat Goodwin, who lives in Scottsdale, Ariz., corroborate some of his claims,presumably including his claim that he was a communications specialist andnational security investigator.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  New York  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910426  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  April  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  319  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday April 26, 199100117015,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>